<seg id="82">VIES system</seg>
<seg id="83">In order to control the application of the VAT exemption claim on intra-communitarian goods supply, a VAT information exchange system has been established within the EU.</seg>
<seg id="84">This includes the VIES electronic system, which allows tax administrators of EU Member States to check whether the supplier was entitled to exempt taxable transactions from VAT and, on the contrary, whether the acquaintant admitted and taxed the goods acquired.</seg>
<seg id="85">VIES information system is not centralized within the EU.</seg>
<seg id="86">Each Member State is developing its own VIES system.</seg>
<seg id="87">National systems work on a common principle and are interconnected through the EU common communication network called. CCN (Common Communication Network; see diagram below).</seg>
<seg id="88">In the Czech Republic, the VIES system was linked to an automated tax information system (hereinafter referred to as ′′ ADIS ′′), in SR with application software of the tax information system (hereinafter referred to as ′′ APV DIS ′′).</seg>
<seg id="89">These systems are used by financial and resp. tax authorities as technical support for executive and management activities in tax and fees management.</seg>
<seg id="90">International administrative cooperation</seg>
<seg id="91">Through international administrative cooperation, the tax administration of each EU member country receives information on tax entities that without this cooperation it would not be able to obtain on its own.</seg>
<seg id="92">The main goal of international administrative cooperation is to combat tax evasion and tax losses.</seg>
<seg id="93">According to Council Regulation (EC) No 1798/2003 Each Member State shall establish a central unit in the field of administrative cooperation between EU Member States in the management of VAT, within the internal organisational structure, called: CLO (Central Liaison Office).</seg>
<seg id="94">In the Czech Republic, the Ministry of Finance - Central Financial and Tax Directorate, where the Department of International Cooperation in VAT Management (hereinafter referred to as ′′ MF CLO ′′ was established).</seg>
<seg id="95">The CLO function in SR is performed by the SR Tax Directorate, the department of international administrative cooperation (DR CLO).</seg>
<seg id="96">These departments, including. communicate with EU foreign administrations especially in the area of information exchange within the VIES system, exchange of spontaneous information and information at the request of EU tax administrations, coordination of multilateral (simultaneous) tax checks, verification of tax identification numbers (hereinafter referred to as 'VAT') persons registered in VAT other EU Member States and communicate with the European Commission.</seg>
<seg id="97">In order to verify a certain intracommunitary transaction or obtain further information related to a particular tax entity, they send financial or responsive information. tax authorities via MF CLO or DR CLO to the EU for information request.</seg>
<seg id="98">Through these applications, they obtain information from the requested Member States which they can use for the correct determination of VAT.</seg>
<seg id="99">Requests for information are sent among the CLO of EU Member States mostly in electronic form using the standardized SCAC form.</seg>
