<seg id="33">The procurement right made substantial changes in 2012</seg>
<seg id="34">The new rules strengthened the transparency of procurement procedures, opened room for more competition and reduced corruption opportunities during the procurement procedure.</seg>
<seg id="35">Fundamental aspects of procurement in both countries</seg>
<seg id="36">As regards European procurement procedures, open and narrower procedures must be applied in both countries.</seg>
<seg id="37">In Germany, contracts below the European limit are awarded in accordance with national rules (public call for competition, limited call for participation, negotiated procedure), but these are virtually identical to the abovementioned conditions for European procurement procedures.</seg>
