<seg id="132">If a contracting authority is involved in the contract, conventions limiting competition or allowing dishonest conduct can weaken confidence in integrity, ability and overall work of public administration.</seg>
<seg id="133">Therefore, prevention of corruption is an essential task of contracting entities.</seg>
<seg id="134">Practice and procedures must be controlled especially in areas particularly prone to corruption in order to allow adequate measures to prevent it.</seg>
<seg id="135">Taking preventive measures and carrying out effective checks can significantly reduce the susceptibility of the decision-making process to corruption.</seg>
