<seg id="116">Alcohol</seg>
<seg id="117">After 2012, the Czech Republic introduced a complex of measures to ensure a detailed overview of the activities of the subjects (see Annex No. 2012). 3, Scheme A) from the production of raw alcohol through marking with control tape to its distribution to the final seller or the legitimate user of the exempt alcohol.</seg>
<seg id="118">In the Czech Republic, customs authorities and production equipment for the production of alcohol that is not in operation is subject to the supervision of customs authorities.</seg>
<seg id="119">The aim of the new regulation was to increase the overview of the processing of alcohol and the production of spirit drinks and to identify persons handling alcohol in the packaging, reduce alcohol management to financially stable and reliable persons and ensure constant supervision of the production and marking of spirits.</seg>
