<seg id="40">Legislation in both countries is based on European Union rules governing this field, in particular on: - Council Directive 92/12 / EEC on general arrangements, holdings, movement and monitoring of excise products (hereinafter referred to as ′′ Directive 92/12 / EEC ′′), - Council Regulation (EC) No 2073/2004 on administrative cooperation in the field of excise duties (hereinafter referred to as ′′ Regulation No 2073/2004 2073/2004 ′′), - Commission Regulation (EEC) No 2073/2004 2719/92 on the accompanying official document for the transport of excise duty products under the excise duty suspension scheme (hereinafter referred to as ′′ Regulation No 2719/92 2719/92 ′′), - Commission Regulation (EEC) No 2719/92 Article 3649/92 (3649/92) of the simplified accompanying document for movement of excise products which have been released for domestic consumption in the Member State of dispatch (hereinafter referred to as ′′ Regulation No 3649/92 3649/92 ′′).</seg>
<seg id="41">The basic legislation governing the issue of excise duties in the Czech Republic is Law No. 353/2003 Coll., on excise duties, as last amended, (hereinafter referred to as ′′ Law No., 353/2003 Coll.") effective from 1. January 2004.</seg>
