<seg id="191">6. Summary</seg>
<seg id="192">The cooperation of the NKÚ-Czech Republic and the NKÚ SR enabled the basic legislation on excise duties in both states, the procedure of the customs authorities of the Czech Republic and the SR in the opening and termination of transport of products under the tax exemption regime between the two states, registration of these transports and further comparing information exchange between customs authorities in international cooperation.</seg>
<seg id="193">6.1 Differences were found by comparing the legislation governing excise duties in the Czech Republic and SR:</seg>
<seg id="194">(a) in the procedure of tax entities and tax managers when initiating the transport of products under the tax exemption scheme.</seg>
<seg id="195">Transport of products under the tax exemption regime can be launched by a tax body in the Czech Republic only with the approval of the tax administrator, who will authorise the start of transportation, provided that transported products were provided with a tax security in the amount of tax on them.</seg>
