<seg id="204">6.2. Customs authorities in both SR and Czech Republic keep electronic records of transport of products under the tax exemption regime.</seg>
<seg id="205">The content and method of keeping this evidence is not regulated by legislation in the Czech Republic or in the SR.</seg>
<seg id="206">Customs authorities in both countries shall register all data from the accompanying documents on the basis of which transport is carried out.</seg>
<seg id="207">There is currently no uniform electronic system for monitoring the transport of goods under the tax exemption regime between Member States of the European Union that allows managers of excise duties in individual Member States to obtain information on the transport of goods in real time.</seg>
<seg id="208">According to Decision 1152/2003 / EC of the European Parliament and of the Council of 16. June 2003, the introduction of an electronic system for monitoring the transport of excise products is envisaged from 1. July 2009</seg>
<seg id="209">Based on the cooperation agreement in the control activity, the Czech party handed over to the Slovak party a database of transport of products under a conditional tax exemption regime started in SR and ended in the Czech Republic.</seg>
