<seg id="525">The statutory rules on control are enshrined in Articles 193-203 of the German fiscal code in Section IV - On-the-spot Tax check. In particular, these articles enshrine rules of admissibility of on-the-spot tax checks (i.e. in the premises of the undertaking), their scope by the subject line, rules on the distribution of responsibilities, form and content of the inspection notification, the principle of control, the tax body's obligation to cooperate and the preconditions for the implementation of the final examination and the communication of the inspection report.</seg>
<seg id="526">On-the-spot tax checks are carried out by responsible financial authorities (Article 195 of the Code).</seg>
<seg id="527">Act on fiscal administration According to Article 5.1 (1) in custody of Article 5.1 (1) Article 19 of the law is the participation in on-the-spot tax checks carried out by the financial authorities for the Federal Central Financial Office.</seg>
<seg id="528">The participating authorities will agree together on the spot the nature and extent of the participation of the Federal Central Tax Office in tax checks.</seg>
<seg id="529">In addition, the Federal Central Tax Office has the right to demand that the specific businesses it select be controlled at the time it determines.</seg>
<seg id="530">In such a case he may declare rules on the execution and content of the inspection at the premises of these companies.</seg>
<seg id="531">The rules on tax checks According to Article 108.7 of the German Constitution, the rules on tax checks (German shortcut BpO 2000) were approved by the Federal Council (Bundesrat, the upper chamber of the German parliament, where the governments of the spolkových are represented).</seg>
<seg id="532">These administrative regulations apply to on-the-spot inspections carried out by the financial authorities of the spolkových and the Federal Central Tax Office.</seg>
